Phase 1: Infrastructure Setup (Dependencies)
1. Create Physical Locations
Locations must exist first so assets have a "home" to go to.

Navigation: Sidebar → Locations → Create New.

Entries: Screen 1, Screen 2, Ticket Counter.

Exam Tip: Keep descriptions brief; the name is the only mandatory field for marks.

2. Define Asset Categories
Categories determine how the system treats the item (e.g., if it's a fixed asset or a consumable).

Navigation: Settings (Gear icon) → Categories → Create New.

Entries: Projectors, Computers, Printers.

Critical Setting: Set Category Type to Asset. (If you select 'Accessory', you won't be able to track movement history properly).

3. Create Asset Models (The Template)
Snipe-IT requires a "Model" before an "Asset." You cannot skip this.

Navigation: Sidebar → Models → Create New.

Entries:

Epson 4K (Category: Projectors)

Dell OptiPlex (Category: Computers)

Thermal Receipt Printer (Category: Printers)

📦 Phase 2: Inventory & Deployment
4. Create the Actual Assets (Hardware)
Navigation: Sidebar → Assets → Create New.

Execution: Create one of each using the Models created in Step 3.

The "Marks" Checkbox: Ensure Status is set to Ready to Deploy.

Note: If status is 'Pending' or 'Archived', the Checkout button will disappear.

5. Assignment (Checkout to Location/Staff)
Action: Go to Assets → List All. Click the blue Checkout button next to an asset.

Targeting: * Checkout to: Select Location.

Location Name: Select Screen 1 or Ticket Counter.

Execution: Click Checkout.

🔄 Phase 3: Movement & Auditing
6. Tracking Movement (The Transfer)
To move an asset from Screen 1 to Screen 2, you must perform a "Checkin/Checkout" cycle.

Checkin: Find the asset → Click Checkin → Note: "Moving to Screen 2."

Checkout: Click Checkout again → Select Location → Screen 2.

7. Verifying the Audit Trail (The Proof)
This is what you show the examiner to prove you "Tracked Movement."

Action: Click the Asset Name (the blue link).

Tab: Click the History tab.

Result: You will see a chronological log: Admin Created → Checked out to Screen 1 → Checked in → Checked out to Screen 2.
